  "prompt": "How can I deactivate Quora?",
  "response": "To deactivate your Quora account, follow these steps:\n\n1. Log into your Quora account\n\n2. Click on your profile picture in the top right corner\n\n3. Select \"Settings\" from the dropdown menu\n\n4. Scroll down to the bottom of the page\n\n5. Look for the \"Deactivate Account\" option (usually near the bottom)\n\n6. Click on \"Deactivate Account\"\n\n7. Quora will ask you to confirm your decision and may prompt you to select a reason for deactivation\n\n8. Complete the deactivation process\n\nImportant notes:\n- Deactivation is different from deletion; your account can be reactivated later\n- Your content will remain on the platform\n- If you want to permanently delete your account, you might need to contact Quora support directly\n\nIf you're having trouble finding the option, you can also try accessing the deactivation page directly by going to: https://www.quora.com/account/deactivate",
